OS_Byte 144  Set vertical shift and interlace
#Parent OS_ByteIndex
=>	R0 =	144
	R1 =	vertical screen shift (as a signed 8 bit number)
	R2 =	interlace flag, 0=on, 1=off

<=	R0 preserved
	R1 =	previous vertical screen shift
	R2 =	previous interlace flag

This call specifies the vertical screen alignment and interlace options after the next mode change. This is equivalent to <*TV=>*Help TV>.
#Line
See <PRM 1, page 650=>PRM-1:650>
